author: Jerry Suppan
reviewText: I very much like the clean, intuitive, simple navigation of this file manager. I one issue I have and that is I am trying to figure out how to give write access to the external 128GB MicroSD card. When I try to copy/paste, or cut/paste objects from one location to the other I am being told I need to choose the root folder of the resource (external MicroSD card) and give it write permissions. But, no where is it clear as to how to do this. At least it is not obvious how to do so. One feature I would like to see is, the ability to copy/cut/paste files from my home network's computer, NAS, etc., over WiFi to my Android device as well. Other then that, wonderful and simple file manager. A big thank you.
